[h1]PhobosLib — Changelog[/h1]

[h2]v1.15.0 — Empty FluidContainer Condition Reset (2026-03-05)[/h2]

[h3]New Function[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]registerEmptyConditionReset(modulePrefix, guardFunc)[/b] — Register a condition reset for empty FluidContainer items. When the player opens or views a container, any empty FluidContainer matching the prefix has its condition restored to ConditionMax. Removes the "(Worn)" suffix from items that repurpose condition as a metadata channel (e.g. purity). Optional guard function controls when resets are active.
[/list]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_VesselReplace[/b] refactored to two-phase system — Condition reset (phase 1) runs before vessel replacement (phase 2) in the same event hook, guaranteeing correct execution order.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.14.0 — World Actions, Entity Rebinding & Fluid Utilities (2026-03-05)[/h2]

[h3]New Modules[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_WorldAction[/b] (client) — Generic world object context menu system. Register custom right-click actions on world objects with requirement checks. Unavailable actions shown in red with reason tooltips.
[*] [b]PhobosLib_EntityRebind[/b] (server) — Server-side entity rebinding for pre-existing world objects. Ensures workstations placed before a mod update get their new entity scripts applied on game load.
[/list]

[h3]New Functions[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]findEmptyFluidContainer()[/b] — Find empty FluidContainer in player inventory matching valid types
[*] [b]tryGetFluidName()[/b] — Safely retrieve fluid type name from a FluidContainer
[*] [b]stampFluidContainerQuality()[/b] — Stamp condition-based purity on filled FluidContainers after +fluid output
[*] [b]recoverDrainedFluidQuality()[/b] — Recover purity from FluidContainers after -fluid drain
[*] [b]getConditionPercent() / setConditionPercent()[/b] — Normalised 0-100% condition helpers regardless of ConditionMax
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] FluidType resolution in tryAddFluid() — resolves string names to FluidType objects for B42 recipe compatibility
[*] Player-vs-inventory parameter handling fixed in find* functions; world action menu deduplication
[*] onContextKey wrapper signature corrected to (player, timePressedContext)
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.13.0 — Popup System & Workstation Labels (2026-02-23)[/h2]

[h3]New Modules[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_Popup[/b] (client) — Generic popup system for PZ B42 mods. Two registration functions:
  [b]registerGuidePopup[/b] — First-time welcome guide with "Don't show again" checkbox, per-character persistence, MP sync.
  [b]registerChangelogPopup[/b] — Version-based "What's New" popup that fires once per major.minor version change with content filtering.
  Queue system shows guides first, then changelogs, one at a time.
[*] [b]PhobosLib_WorkstationLabel[/b] (client) — Automatically filters untranslated tags (e.g. CannotBeResearched) from the crafting window's "Requires: ..." workstation label. Supports both vanilla and Neat Crafting UIs. No public API — fully self-contained.
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] Workstation label filter now hooks Neat Crafting's NC_RecipeInfoPanel when installed
[*] Changelog popup correctly detects fresh installs (nil stored version = show all)
[*] buildContent callback now receives lastSeenVersion for filtering
[*] Corrected translation table reference from IG_UI to IGUI
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.12.0 — Powered Workstations (2026-02-23)[/h2]

[h3]New Module[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_Power[/b] (client) — Powered CraftBench entity support with 5 public functions:
  [b]isGridPowerActive()[/b] — Check if the electrical grid is still on.
  [b]hasPower(square)[/b] — Check any power source (grid, generator, custom).
  [b]registerPowerSource(checkFunc)[/b] — Register custom power sources (e.g. battery+inverter).
  [b]registerPoweredCraftBench(entity, options)[/b] — Register an entity as requiring electricity. Greys out craft button with tooltip when no power. Options: messageKey, drainPerMinute, guardFunc.
  [b]startPowerDrain / stopPowerDrain[/b] — Time-based generator fuel drain sessions.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.11.0 — Farming Sprays & Tooltip Guards (2026-02-22)[/h2]

[h3]New Module[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_FarmingSpray[/b] (client) — Register custom crop cure sprays that appear in the B42 "Treat Problem" submenu and respond to the Interact hotkey on diseased plants. Hooks ISFarmingMenu and CFarming_Interact, pcall-wrapped. Supports Mildew, Flies, Aphids, and Slugs cure types.
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] Tooltip render replacement now guards against nil self.tooltip during edge-case render calls, preventing crashes when multiple tooltip-modifying mods are active
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Summary[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]22 modules[/b] total (12 shared + 10 client/server)
[*] [b]~120 public functions[/b]
[*] New since v1.14.0: registerEmptyConditionReset() API, two-phase VesselReplace system
[/list]
